{"id":"atg-tournament-runner-ufh","title":"Web-based tournament execution UI","description":"Add a web UI for configuring and running tournaments, eliminating the need for complex CLI commands.\n\n## User flow:\n1. docker run -p 8080:8080 ghcr.io/.../atg-tournament-runner\n2. Open http://localhost:8080\n3. Add players (network URLs or built-in strategies)\n4. Configure rounds, games per player\n5. Click Run - see live progress\n6. View animated results\n\n## Components:\n- Tournament config form (players, rounds, settings)\n- REST API: POST /api/tournaments to start\n- Async execution with WebSocket progress updates\n- Progress indicator (current round, games completed)\n- Integration with existing results viewer\n\n## Dependencies:\n- Requires atg-tournament-runner-gpm (viewer port) to be completed first","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"jdelfino@brandeis.edu","created_at":"2026-02-03T15:24:24.310981509Z","created_by":"Joe Delfino","updated_at":"2026-02-03T15:24:24.310981509Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"atg-tournament-runner-ufh","depends_on_id":"atg-tournament-runner-gpm","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-03T15:24:28.693243511Z","created_by":"Joe Delfino"}]}
